Instruction: Measure the DC voltage and continuity of the control (ambient sensor) module’s own supply rails: first, with power on, probe the module’s internal V+ and ground nodes relative to the PSU negative to confirm a stable ~12 V with no 20‑s dips. Then, with power off, check continuity from the PSU positive cable to the control module’s internal V+ node, and from the PSU negative cable to the control module’s internal ground reference, to detect any high‑resistance or intermittent connections that could cause internal oscillation while leaving the output cables steady.
