e PSU Output Cable (+) and/or (−) fast‑connection terminal at the power‑supply module, for example an intermittent or high‑resistance mechanical contact within the connector housing. Replacing or repairing this specific connector pair (treating them as components) should resolve the discrepancy between continuity tests and observed operation and eliminate the perceived intermittent behavior.'
